            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Ex auctoritate <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>eratoris</ex></expan> Caesaris divi <lb n="3"/>Traiani Parthici <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilii</ex></expan> <lb n="4"/>divi Nervae nepotis <lb n="5"/>Traiani Hadriani <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pontif</abbr><ex>icis</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>max</abbr><ex>imi</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>trib</abbr><ex>unicia</ex></expan> <lb n="7"/><expan><abbr>potest</abbr><ex>ate</ex></expan> VIII <expan><abbr>imp</abbr><ex>eratoris</ex></expan> IIII co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ulis</ex></expan> III <lb n="8"/><expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan> Messius Rusticus curator <lb n="9"/>alvei et riparum Tiberis et <lb n="10"/><supplied reason="lost">cloacar</supplied>um urbis <expan><abbr>r</abbr><ex>ecto</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>r</abbr><ex>igore</ex></expan> restituit <lb n="11"/><supplied reason="lost">sec</supplied>undum praecedentem <lb n="12"/>terminationem proximi cippi <lb n="13"/><expan><abbr>ped</abbr><ex>es</ex></expan> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>(B): Fornari, AE 1917/18: geringfügig abweichende Textwiedergabe; keine Unterscheidung des jeweils eigenen Erhaltungszustandes der beiden (CIL VI 40865. 40866) nahezu identischen Inschrifttexte. Terminalcippus.</p>
